    <note>Zhao(1) Chongmu [11842] When Liu(2) Guangzu [10658] was prefect of Xiangling and therefore Military Governor of Hubei, he directly recruited Chongmu as a secretary. At the same time, he also directly recruited the younger brother of Zhao(1) Shishao (Taizu descendant not in dataset). Chongmu pointed out that when Shishao was chief of the Imperial Apothecary (yaoju), he requested that Zhao(1) Ruyu [3200] be beheaded in order to gain the gratitude of the world. Chongmu noted that this made it immpossible to serve with Shishao's younger brother. Guangzu dismissed the younger brother of Shishao and retained Chongmu. Chongmu was not included in the imperial genealogies. CBD, 4, 3566-67.</note>
